field.value:
Registered components are implicitly constrained to be reference types, however the Register() methods don't throw exceptions when a value type is registered. This should be explicit to reduce confusion.

// Current
var kernel = DefaultKernel();
kernel.Register(Component.For<Int32>().Named("1").Instance(1));  // No exception

// Expected
var kernel = DefaultKernel();
kernel.Register(Component.For<Int32>().Named("1").Instance(1));  // Throws exception
